<h1>What is the best/safest way to cast void* to char* in c++?</h1>  <p>static_cast or reinterpret_cast?</p>  <pre><code>void I2C::Read(void* buffer, DWORD address, UINT size)  {     if (_isDeviceAvailable)     {         _iicInstance.seekg(address, std::ios_base::beg);         _iicInstance.read(reinterpret_cast&lt;char *&gt;(buffer), size);         Gpio::SVSet();     } </code></pre>  <p>}</p>